title: For Sale/Trade:  German Deutsche Werk Ortgies .32ACP W/Ammo, Extra Mags, Owner's Manual, Extras
postcontent:
Very good condition German made Ortgies 7.65mm (.32ACP). This gun is the commercial version, and the 6th variant (there were six model variants?). The Ortgies pocket pistols were made (officially) from 1919 to 1924. This particular gun (according to the serial number) was made around 1922-23. The Orgies semi-automatic pistols were excellent, well made guns. The design was ahead of its time. This gun has the factory original 7rd magazine. Overall, this gun is in very good condition. Has all matching numbers (barrel, frame, slide). Bluing is in really good condition for its age (this gun is at least 90 years old). All original finish, not re-blued, or anything like that. Has factory wood grips. The grips has no cracks, splits, or damages. Has a few minor dents and dings. Barrel is in very good condition - has a few minor surface rust. Bore is in very good condition, however it has a few minor rust (the Germans or people back in the old days used highly corrosive ammo). In addition, there's an old Ortgies owner's manual. It's really worn out, tattered, but all the pages are there (but not intact - it looks like as old as the gun itself). You must be at least 21 years old or older and have a valid Kentucky driver's license (KY CCDW okay) to buy/trade this gun. Local (Kentucky) sale/trade only. No shipping out of state. Just email me with any questions. Serious inquiries only please. Thanks for looking.

 -- Below is an excerpt from one of the Ortgies websites. It is not my own. I am just giving a credit to the author/creator of that particular website. You can do a google (or yahoo) search on this particular pistol on the internet. There are several Ortgies websites on line --

 " The Ortgies pistol has a number of unusual design features. The most obvious is its grip safety which, once squeezed, stays in the “fire” position without further pressure of the hand on the grip. A button on the left side of the gun allows the grip safety to pop back out. Since the grip safety is powered by the striker spring, the safety can only be popped out, i.e., placed in the “safe” position, when the striker is cocked. Hence, if the safety is enabled, the gun is cocked. When the grip safety is enabled, the sear is prevented from moving downward and the tension on the striker spring is reduced. Pressing the safety- enabling button also allows the slide to be lifted off the frame rail for disassembly. The striker serves as the ejector. "

 Gun comes with the following:

 - 70 rounds of non-corrosive ammo (50rds of American Eagle FMJ and 20rds of Speer Gold Dot hollow points)

title: For Sale:  Your freedom for sale - $0

Stop selling your "Assault Rifles".

This is exactly what the state wants you to do. They cannot imprison and felonize all holders of "Assault Rifles" - it's physically, financially, and legally impossible to do so.

Do not register them either - common sense and history proves that this registry is for confiscation down the road. Irrefutably guaranteed. So why do it?

You're going to let your state or government tell you that you can't defend yourself with 30+ rounds of continuous semi automatic fire in the event of an emergency or national/global disaster? That's just silly. It's your life, you should be able to adequately defend it.

Just remember, it will be DHS walking around with "Assault Rifles" in the event of a national disaster - do you want to be under-armed if they are not operating ethically towards you or your community? Let me be more clear - do you want them raping, pillaging, and stealing without an adequate ability to resist these actions? A lever action rifle, shotgun, or pistol is not adequate against military-grade, semi-auto rifles.

The out of state FFL's are taking you guys for a ride by undermining the prices of these guns when they purchase them from you. They have to make money as a business, but they also understand you're desperate to sell them because you don't want to be a "felon". title: For Sale:  Springfield XDM .45 4.5" + Range Pack + Ammo
postcontent:
This .45 acp XDm is in amazing condition with a very low round count. I recently put a good bit of time into polishing the barrel and the guide rod. Gives the gun a very sharp/clean/intimidating look. I did NOT do mirror finish because I think the brushed aluminum look is very sharp and a bit easier to keep looking clean. The feed ramp has been well polished to a mirror like finish and ammo slides into position VERY easily. Ejects ammo beautifully as well. Has been well cleaned (ask me for pictures of my other weapons and you will see the OCD I have. I am also INCLUDING x2 magazines of ammo which is 26 rounds. This is 230 grain 45 FMJ ammo. The XDm features: grip safety (1911 style; I prefer this to the Glock angled grip), loaded chamber indicator, striker status indicator (This feature is NOT on a Glock), MATCH GRADE barrel, Major Grasp serrations (front and back of slide), minimal reset trigger (one of the smoothest I’ve felt on a 45) and fixed dovetail white 3-dot sights. 

Pistol package includes: (2) 13-round magazines, 26 rounds of 230 grain 45 ammo, molded holster and mag pouch, mag loading tool, cable lock, heavy-duty plastic case, and owner's manual.

Pricing: This package sells for right around 689.99. Fairly hard to find in the 4.5". The polishing of the barrel and guide rod is a bit expensive addition @ $50+ from someone and the extra 26 rounds (approx. $10) make this deal very fair. No rush to sell.
